            Tags = """["admin","quiz"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"passingScore":75,"questionsPerQuiz":10,"shuffleOptions":true,"showExplanationsAfterSubmit":true,"questions":[{"id":"ad1","text":"A new employee needs to be set up in Forge. What is the correct process?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Go to Admin → Users, click Add User, set their password, and give them their login credentials"},{"id":"b","text":"Go to Admin → Users, click Add User, fill in their details — the system generates a setup token the employee uses to set their own password","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Ask the employee to self-register on the login page and then approve their account"},{"id":"d","text":"Create their profile in Account → Profile and assign a temporary password"}],"explanation":"Admins never set passwords. The system generates a secure setup token URL. Share this with the employee — they follow the link to set their own password and complete their account."},{"id":"ad2","text":"You want to add a new kanban board for tracking maintenance work orders. Where do you do this?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Kanban Board → Settings → Add Board"},{"id":"b","text":"Admin → Track Types → New Track Type — define the name, code, and stages","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Admin → Settings → Board Configuration"},{"id":"d","text":"You cannot add new board types — only the default ones are available"}],"explanation":"Track types define kanban boards. Go to Admin → Track Types and click New Track Type. Define the stages with names, codes, colors, WIP limits, and irreversibility flags."},{"id":"ad3","text":"An employee is leaving the company. What should you do with their account?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Delete their account from Admin → Users"},{"id":"b","text":"Toggle their Is Active switch to OFF — this prevents login but preserves all historical data","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Remove their role so they can't access anything"},{"id":"d","text":"Change their password to something random"}],"explanation":"Never delete user accounts. Toggle Is Active to OFF to deactivate. The user can no longer log in, but all their historical data (jobs, time entries, expenses, activity logs) remains intact for reporting and compliance."},{"id":"ad4","text":"Your company just opened a second warehouse. How do you register it in the system?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Admin → Settings → Company Locations → New Location — enter name, address, and state","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Inventory → Locations → Create Warehouse"},{"id":"c","text":"Admin → Integrations → Add Location"},{"id":"d","text":"You can only have one location in Forge"}],"explanation":"Company locations are managed in Admin → Settings → Locations. Add the new location with its name and address. Employees assigned to this location will get the correct state withholding forms."},{"id":"ad5","text":"You want to rename 'Jobs' to 'Work Orders' throughout the entire application. Where do you make this change?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Admin → Settings → Application Name"},{"id":"b","text":"Admin → Terminology — find the Jobs label and enter 'Work Orders' as the custom label","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"This can't be changed — the built-in labels are fixed"},{"id":"d","text":"Admin → Reference Data → Jobs group → rename the label"}],"explanation":"The Terminology tab lets you customize any application label. Find the Jobs label, enter 'Work Orders', and click Save. The change applies immediately across the entire app for all users."},{"id":"ad6","text":"A track type stage is marked as 'Irreversible'. What does this mean?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The stage name cannot be renamed or edited"},{"id":"b","text":"Jobs in this stage cannot move backward to a previous stage — typically because accounting documents (invoices, payments) are attached","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Only admins can move jobs into this stage"},{"id":"d","text":"The stage has reached its WIP limit and no more jobs can enter"}],"explanation":"Irreversible stages prevent backward movement. This is used for stages with accounting documents attached (Invoice, Payment) where moving a job backward would create financial inconsistencies."},{"id":"ad7","text":"You need to see who changed a system setting last Tuesday. Where do you look?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Admin → Audit Log — filter the record type to system settings and set the date range","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Admin → Settings → Change History"},{"id":"c","text":"Reports → Admin Activity"},{"id":"d","text":"There is no audit trail for settings changes"}],"explanation":"The Audit Log records every change to every record, including system settings. Filter the record type to system settings and pick the day to see exactly who changed what, with the before and after values."},{"id":"ad8","text":"You're configuring QuickBooks Online integration. What happens after you click 'Connect QuickBooks'?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"You enter your QBO credentials directly in Forge"},{"id":"b","text":"You're sent to Intuit's own sign-in and approval screen to authorize the connection","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Forge downloads your QBO data automatically without any authorization"},{"id":"d","text":"A support ticket is created to manually connect the systems"}],"explanation":"You never type your QuickBooks password into Forge. Clicking Connect sends you to Intuit's own screen, where you sign in and approve the connection. You're then returned with the connection active."},{"id":"ad9","text":"An employee's badge is not being recognized at the kiosk. Where do you check their scan identifier?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Admin → Teams & Kiosks → Badge Management"},{"id":"b","text":"Admin → Users → edit the user → Scan Identifiers section","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Account → Security → Badge Settings"},{"id":"d","text":"The kiosk terminal itself has a badge registration screen"}],"explanation":"The badges and tags a person scans at a kiosk are managed per-user in Admin → Users. Edit the user and look at the Scan Identifiers section to add, remove, or verify their badge ID."},{"id":"ad10","text":"You want to require all managers to use MFA (multi-factor authentication). Where do you configure this?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Admin → Settings → Security → MFA Settings"},{"id":"b","text":"Admin → MFA Policy — select 'Manager' in the Required for Roles multi-select and click Save","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Each manager must enable MFA individually from their Account → Security"},{"id":"d","text":"MFA is all-or-nothing — you cannot enforce it by role"}],"explanation":"The MFA Policy tab lets you select which roles require MFA. Select Manager (and any other roles), click Save. Users in those roles will be prompted to set up an authenticator app on their next sign-in."},{"id":"ad11","text":"A compliance template shows a 'No Form Definition' warning. What does this mean?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The template was created but no employees have submitted it yet"},{"id":"b","text":"The template doesn't have a form definition — you need to upload a PDF and run field extraction, or manually configure the fields","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The template is disabled and needs to be reactivated"},{"id":"d","text":"The PDF upload failed and needs to be retried"}],"explanation":"A 'No Form Definition' warning means the template exists but has no fillable fields yet. Click Extract Definition to upload a PDF and let the AI find the fields, or set up the fields yourself."},{"id":"ad12","text":"You need to add a new expense category called 'Travel - Lodging' to the system. How is this done?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Expenses page → Settings → Categories"},{"id":"b","text":"The Admin → Reference Data screen is read-only, so you request the new category from whoever set up your install; once added, it appears there and in the expense form","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Admin → Settings → System Settings → Expense Categories"},{"id":"d","text":"Admin → Reference Data → expand the Expense Categories group → click Add Item"}],"explanation":"Reference-data lists (including expense categories) are set up for your install during onboarding, not entered in-app. The Admin → Reference Data screen lets you review the existing values in a read-only table but has no Add, Edit, or reorder controls. Ask whoever configured your install to add the new category; once it is in, it shows up there and in the expense form dropdown."},{"id":"ad13","text":"The track type code field only accepts a specific format. What is it?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Any text is allowed — there are no format restrictions"},{"id":"b","text":"Uppercase letters, numbers, and underscores only (e.g., PRODUCTION, R_AND_D)","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Lowercase letters and hyphens (e.g., production, r-and-d)"},{"id":"d","text":"Numeric codes only (e.g., 001, 002)"}],"explanation":"Track type codes accept only uppercase letters, numbers, and underscores. This keeps them consistent, since a code is a fixed identifier once saved."},{"id":"ad14","text":"What happens when you lock a pay period through a specific date?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Employees cannot submit expenses after that date"},{"id":"b","text":"Time entries on or before that date can no longer be modified by employees or managers","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The payroll report for that period is automatically generated"},{"id":"d","text":"All jobs due before that date are automatically archived"}],"explanation":"Pay period locking prevents modifications to time entries within the locked period. This ensures payroll data integrity once it has been processed."},{"id":"ad15","text":"You created a new training module but employees can't see it. What is the most likely issue?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The module hasn't been added to a training path yet"},{"id":"b","text":"The module's Published toggle is set to OFF — employees only see published modules","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The module's content type is not supported by the training viewer"},{"id":"d","text":"New modules require a system restart to appear"}],"explanation":"Training modules have a Published toggle. When OFF (Draft), the module is invisible to regular users. Toggle it ON in Admin → Training → Content tab to make it visible."}]}"""
        });

        // ── Existing modules (migrated from original seed) ───────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Admin: Managing Users and Roles",
            Slug = "admin-users-and-roles",
            Summary = "For admins and managers: how to create users, assign roles, configure kiosk access, and manage teams.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 7,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 5,
            AppRoutes = """["/admin"]""",
            Tags = """["admin"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Admin: Managing Users and Roles\n\nUser management in Forge is handled through the Admin panel. Only users with the Admin or Manager role can access this area.\n\n### Creating a New User\n\nNavigate to **Admin → Users** and click **New User**. Fill in the user's name, email address, and role. Do NOT set a password — the system generates a secure setup token and emails it to the new user. The employee follows the link to set their own password and complete their account.\n\n### Roles\n\nForge uses additive roles:\n\n- **Engineer** — kanban board, assigned work, time tracking, expenses, files\n- **Production Worker** — simplified task list, start/stop timer, move cards, notes\n- **PM** — backlog, planning, leads, reporting (read-only board)\n- **Manager** — everything PM + assign work, approve expenses, set priorities\n- **Office Manager** — customer/vendor, invoice queue, employee documents\n- **Admin** — everything + user management, roles, system settings, track types\n\n### Kiosk Auth (Badge + PIN)\n\nFor shop floor workers who don't use a computer, set up badge sign-in at the kiosk. In the user's profile, assign an employee barcode (printed on their badge). The worker scans their badge at a kiosk and enters a 4–6 digit PIN to clock in, start timers, and move jobs.\n\n### Teams\n\nOrganize users into teams under **Admin → Teams**. Teams are used for filtered board views (a lane per team), workload reporting, and shift scheduling.\n\n### Deactivating Users\n\nWhen an employee leaves, deactivate their account from Admin → Users. Deactivated users cannot log in but all their historical data (jobs, time entries, expenses) is preserved.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "System Settings and Branding",
            Slug = "system-settings-branding",
            Summary = "How to configure application settings, company profile, brand colors, logo, and company locations.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 6,
            AppRoutes = """["/admin/settings"]""",
            Tags = """["admin","settings","branding"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## System Settings and Branding\n\n### Company Profile\n\nNavigate to **Admin → Settings → Company Profile**. Enter your company's legal name, phone number, email, EIN, and website. This information appears on invoices, packing slips, and other customer-facing documents.\n\n### Company Locations\n\nUnder **Admin → Settings → Locations**, add all your physical locations (main office, warehouse, remote sites). Each location has a name, address, and state. Mark one as the Default — this is the default work location for employees who haven't specified one, and it drives state withholding form requirements.\n\n### Brand Colors and Logo\n\nIn **Admin → Settings**, scroll to the Brand section. Choose your primary and accent brand colors. These update the entire app's color theme in real time — all users see the change immediately.\n\nTo upload your company logo, click the Logo section and drag your image file (PNG or SVG recommended). The logo appears in the header bar and on printed documents.\n\n### Application Settings\n\nThe Settings panel also has configuration for:\n- **Application name** — shown in the browser tab and header\n- **Planning cycle duration** — default length for new planning cycles\n- **Auto-archive days** — how long after completion before jobs auto-archive\n- **Max upload size** — maximum file attachment size\n- **Email notifications** — enable/disable system emails\n\n### Pay Period Locking\n\nThe Settings tab also holds **Pay Period Locking**. Pick a date in **Lock entries through** and click **Lock Period**. After confirming, every unlocked time entry on or before that date is frozen — employees and managers can no longer edit or delete it, which protects payroll data once it has been processed. A confirmation message reports how many entries were locked.\n\nLocking is one-directional and the confirmation warns it cannot be undone, so lock only after the period's time is final. The deliberate exception is **Admin → Time Corrections**: an admin can still correct a locked entry there, and that path keeps a correction-history record and notifies the affected employee, so the change stays auditable.","sections":[]}"""
        });

