            Tags = """["admin","integrations","quickbooks"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Integration Configuration\n\nNavigate to **Admin → Integrations** to configure external service connections.\n\n### QuickBooks Online\n\nForge syncs with QuickBooks Online for accounting. To connect:\n1. Click **Connect QuickBooks** — you'll be sent to Intuit's own sign-in and approval screen.\n2. Sign in to your QBO account and approve the connection.\n3. You're returned to the app with the connection active.\n\nOnce connected, the following sync automatically:\n- Customers (bidirectional)\n- Items/Products (from QB)\n- Invoices (Forge → QB)\n- Payments (Forge → QB)\n- Vendor Bills from POs (Forge → QB)\n- Time Activities (Forge → QB for payroll)\n\nNote: When QuickBooks is connected, some features (invoicing, payments, AR aging) are read-only in Forge — manage them in QBO directly.\n\n### Outgoing Email\n\nFor the emails the app sends (setup links, notifications, invoice delivery), point it at your email provider under **Integrations → Email**. Enter the mail server address, the sign-in details your provider gave you, and the address the mail comes from. Use the **Test Connection** button to send a test email to yourself before saving.\n\n### File Storage\n\nCustomer files, photos, and attachments are kept in the app's file storage. On a standard install this is already set up for you and needs no attention. If your company keeps files with an outside storage provider instead, enter the connection details that provider gave you here.\n\n### Test Mode\n\nDuring setup or a trial run, an install can be put in a test mode that skips every outside service and returns stand-in responses, so you can try things out without live credentials. This is turned on when the app is first installed — not something you toggle day to day.","sections":[]}"""
