            Slug = "admin-time-corrections",
            Summary = "How managers and admins correct an employee's time entry: filter, edit date/start/end, supply a required reason, and read the correction history.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 6,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 17,
            AppRoutes = """["/admin/time-corrections"]""",
            Tags = """["admin","time-tracking","corrections"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Time Corrections\n\nEmployees sometimes forget to clock out, fat-finger a start time, or log to the wrong day. **Admin → Time Corrections** lets a Manager or Admin fix an existing time entry while keeping a permanent record of what was changed and why. This tab is available to **Managers and Admins** (not regular workers).\n\n### Finding the Entry\n\nThe top of the panel has three filters: an **Employee** dropdown plus a **From Date** and **To Date** range. Pick the employee and narrow the dates to the shift in question. The **Time Entries** table below lists matching entries with their date, start, stop, and duration.\n\n### Making a Correction\n\nClick the **edit (pencil)** icon on the entry you want to fix. The Correct Time Entry dialog opens with the original values shown read-only at the top (employee, original date, start, end, duration) so you always have the before-picture in front of you. Then adjust any of:\n\n- **Date** — move the entry to the correct day\n- **Start Time** and **End Time** — fix the clock-in/clock-out\n- **Category** and **Notes** — optional reclassification\n\nWhen you set both a start and end time, the dialog **auto-calculates the duration** and previews it (\"Calculated duration: …\") so you can sanity-check before saving.\n\n### The Reason Is Required\n\nThe **Reason for Correction** field is mandatory — Save stays disabled until you fill it in. This is the heart of the feature: it is what makes a correction auditable rather than a silent edit. Write a short, honest reason (\"Employee forgot to clock out; confirmed actual stop time of 4:30 PM with supervisor\").\n\n### What Happens on Save\n\nSaving does three things:\n\n1. **Snapshots the original** values into a correction-history record before applying your changes.\n2. **Applies** the new date/time/category/notes to the live entry (admins are not blocked by pay-period date locks).\n3. **Notifies the affected employee** automatically, including the reason you entered — there are no silent changes to someone's pay record.\n\n### Correction History\n\nBelow the entries table, the **Correction History** table is the audit trail. Each row records when the correction was made and the *original* date, start, end, and duration — so you can always see what an entry looked like before it was touched. Use it to answer \"who changed this and what did it used to say?\"\n\n### Relationship to Pay-Period Locking\n\nLocking a pay period (Admin → Settings) freezes time entries so employees and managers can't modify them. Admin time corrections are the deliberate, audited exception path: an admin can still correct an entry, and the history + employee notification keep the change accountable.","sections":[]}"""
